## ğŸ§­ System Context

The **Hazards Transformation Layer** ensures that all incoming hazard datasets â€” tornado, flood, wildfire, and drought â€” are spatially harmonized and metadata-aligned for integration with downstream validation and AI systems.

**Core Responsibilities:**
- Reproject all spatial datasets to **EPSG:4326** for global interoperability.  
- Normalize NetCDF, GeoTIFF, and shapefile attributes per **CF conventions**.  
- Conduct spatial resampling and tiling (COG/PMTiles formats).  
- Validate metadata and coordinate alignment with ISO/FAIR+CARE standards.  
- Register transformation traces and hashes into the Governance Ledger.

> *â€œTransformation is not change â€” itâ€™s alignment with truth.â€*

